    <textTemplates>
        <name>outstandingInfo</name>
        <isViewedAsPlainText>true</isViewedAsPlainText>
        <text>{!$Record.OW_advice__r.Additional_Questions_to_be_asked_on_call__c}
Steps required by partner:
- spend max 15 minutes before call doing the following prep work
- open most recent lifeline on a tab (review assumptions slide)
- read through and reacquaint yourself with facts
- have spending in the profile open on a tab and/or a budget planner 
- have the cash page of profile open on a tab 
- don&apos;t commit to remodelling the lifeline - this will be decided by you/planning based on the answers below after the catch up call
- remember to update client vulnerability assessment

Ask the following questions:
- Any major changes since we last spoke/expected by the end of the current tax year?
- If job has changed: can you give me details of your new employer pension (need policy number) and workplace benefits for us to check before we meet?
- How much income will you make in this tax year? (prompt client for employment/relevant earnings/dividends/investments/property income)
- What is your current cash position? (both parties) (ideally have the cash page open on SF profile to cross reference live on the call)
- Any big expenses coming up in next 3-5 years? (and if they need further prompting -&gt; specifically around property and kids/schools etc.)
- Updates to spending: 1) please confirm your current spending (compare to what&apos;s in the profile) and 2) confirm modelled spending in the future (retirement) for lifeline (reference last LL modelling assumptions)
- mortgage rate expiry date/changes to mortgage: check mortgage page on SF and ask client for verbal update
- Changes to existing non-NOVA products: Have you made any contributions to other assets/new assets added/assets sold or closed/new liabilities and liabilities paid off?

Documentation:
&quot;You may or may not have already sent these through, but can I just check, have you sent us:&quot;
Accumulation clients
- Latest tax year&apos;s P60/P45
- Tax return
- State pension forecast &amp; NIC record 

Decumulation clients
- Updated budget planner</text>
